entries.title: Turn your radiators down! Turn off appliances! Latest advice in new energy saving campaign
entries.description: Consumers will also be told to turn off appliances when not in use and to draught-proof their windows and doors by putting blankets under them.

entries.title: HelloFresh customer finds maggots in her mince meat as meal delivery giant
entries.description: A devoted customer of meal-kit service Hello Fresh was horrified on Wednesday after finding maggots in the meat she'd ordered, and revealed her terrible experience with their customer service.

entries.title: Parents of The Crown star who battled childhood cancer hail their boy's bravery
entries.description: The 13-year-old Netflix star was diagnosed with leukaemia at the age of just 21 months and battled the disease for three years until he was given the all-clear.

entries.title: Nigerian chess prodigy, 12, who rose to fame while living in a homeless shelter gets granted asylum
entries.description: Tanitoluwa 'Tani' Adewumi's family - including Tani's mother, father and 19-year-old brother -arrived in New York in 2017, as his Christian brood were forced to flee Nigeria.

entries.title: David Howard: Truck driver charged after dad found dead on the side of a Hume Highway
entries.description: David Howard, 30, was found on the side of the Hume Highway near Campbelltown, in Sydney's south-west, on October 12 by police searching the scene after being alerted to a possible fatality

entries.title: Wieambilla shooting: Radio messages from police helicopter as Train family ambushed cops
entries.description: The last dying moments of the Doomsday death cult family have been revealed in a series of messages from aerial surveillance police in a chopper watching from above as the gunfight raged below.

entries.title: SECOND suburban husband indicted for smuggling nuclear weapon tech to Russia
entries.description: A second key figure in the plot to smuggle weapons components from America to Russia is also a suburban husband who lives in a luxury $1m New Jersey home with his wife and their young children.

entries.title: Security limits on cabin bag liquids and removal of laptops rule will be axed by next summer
entries.description: The ban on air passengers carrying more than 100ml of liquids in their hand luggage will be lifted at most major UK airports by June 2024, ministers announced last night.

entries.title: Tornado hits New Orleans as flash flood warning is issued in Louisiana amid severe weather crisis
entries.description: A large tornado landed in downtown New Orleans on Wednesday afternoon just after 4:00 pm a day after a similar storm devastated a small community in the northern part of Louisiana.

entries.title: Huge magnitude 6.3 earthquake strikes offshore near Alaska's Amchitka Island
entries.description: A massive earthquake with a magnitude of 6.3 struck offshore near Alaska's Amchitka Island and officials have warned aftershocks are likely.

entries.title: White House to restart free COVID home testing program
entries.description: The Biden administration will restart its program to send free COVID-19 tests to Americans during the winter months when another coronavirus spike is expected.

entries.title: Tory Lanez 'threatened to shoot Megan Thee Stallion's ex-assistant'
entries.description: Megan Thee Stallion's assistant revealed Tory Lanez threatened to shoot her before opening fire on the singer's feet.

entries.title: Melting ice caps will help CHINA penetrate the Atlantic, Britain's Chief of the Defence Staff warns
entries.description: A recession of the ice caps would see trading and shipping routes open up between Europe and Asia, but would also enable China's rapidly expanding navy to patrol the High North

entries.title: Mother of toddler Quinton Simon is indicted on 19 counts
entries.description: Leilani Simon, 22, is facing charges including malice murder, felony murder, concealment of death and making false statements to police in the death of her 20-month-old son Quinton Simon.

entries.title: 'It's a significant issue': University chiefs must defend free speech on campus, watchdog warns
entries.description: Susan Lapworth, chief executive of the Office for Students (OfS), said academic freedom has become a major issue in universities. The Ofs has launched an Insight brief.

entries.title: Rishi Sunak reveals his Hindu faith provides 'strength' and prays with his daughters before bedtime
entries.description: In a candid interview, the Prime Minister said Hinduism is not just a religion but a 'way of life' that instils the values of service, duty and strong family bonds

entries.title: Hedges, homegrown herbs and swimming PONDS will be all the rage in Britain next year, experts say
entries.description: People are also turning towards 'planet friendly gardening', the RHS said in its predictions based on input from gardeners, experts and growers.
